QUALIFICATION: as a subgenus of Esox; Esox truttaceus listed as new species in footnote by Cuvier, but no description given and McDowall 1967 regarded truttaceus from that work as a nomen nudum; alternately one could argue that that name was a reference to the generic definition and covered the new species description, making that type species by monotypy; Cuvier also listed truttaceus as a possible synonym of Esox argenteus Forster, which as a conditional assignment has no status, therefore we follow McDowall 1967 here.
